Description: Fragment of flattened handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-brown; a little mica.
Curator's comments: Name Apollodoros. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.28a, 19. From same die as a piece from the Rhodian Peraia, Bybassos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0926)
